news.title: In a first, BMC to auction two seized choppers over property tax dues
news.para: Civic officials said the BMC had seized two helicopters from a company which had not paid property tax to the tune of Rs 4.1 crore.

news.title: Construction of aqua line extension to Greater Noida west may begin this year
news.para: Officials in the Noida Metro Rail Corporation (NMRC) are expecting the Centre’s approval by the end of November. That will pave the way for construction to begin in December.

news.title: Bihar: Sand mining to resume in eight districts from today
news.para: Sources said the mining in the remaining eight districts would be resumed after getting clearance from the state cabinet. The auction of authorised mining ghats will be done after the cabinet’s nod.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC reserves order in case of floor-wise sale of properties
news.para: The UT administration had submitted before the HC that no NOC was issued mentioning floor of property. On the HC directions, the UT had submitted an affidavit of assistant estate officer (AEO) Harjeet Singh Sandhu.

news.title: Goa: Soon, get email notifications for land partition requests
news.para: In a bid to reduce fraud in property transactions, the government has also created a system to notify individuals every time someone applies for partition of a plot in a particular village.

news.title: Chandigarh: Traders seek implementation of apartment act
news.para: The demands were raised by a delegation of CBM under the chairmanship of CBM president Charanjiv Singh before UT adviser Dharam Pal.

news.title: HC seeks reply from Rajasthan government on planned land deed campaign
news.para: The petition mentioned that the master plan had been ignored. A drafted parallel master plan had been prepared by the state government to do away with the provisions of the initial master plan.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to set up 25 'work from home' townships
news.para: The government has decided to set up 25 townships on pilot basis and go for expansion after studying the situation. The government will provide space, work stations, high-speed internet and other infrastructure in the proposed townships.

news.title: Environment ministry approves Mumbai's coastal zone management plan
news.para: The decision is also expected to make way for the redevelopment of a large number of eligible housing societies and slums, as these areas can now get a floor-space index (FSI) or permissible development equal to that for the rest of the city.

news.title: Builder to install safety grilles in three flats: Maharashtra consumer body
news.para: The builder, through advocate Akhil Rao, contested her right to be heard as a “consumer” as it was a redevelopment project. He said theirs was a “tenant-landlord relationship”.

news.title: Navi Mumbai builder fails to appear, Bombay HC orders NBW
news.para: The MahaRERA had earlier issued a recovery warrant for the same and had also imposed a penalty of Rs 10 lakh on the builder. The couple had booked a 2 BHK for Rs 25 lakh in January 2012, and possession of the flat was to be given in 2014.

news.title: Delhi government extends 20% reduction in circle rates till December 31
news.para: Kejriwal said, "The 20% rebate in circle rates will continue. We will not let anything trouble Delhi people during this pandemic. We will stand with Delhi people at every front and every step."

news.title: Gurugram: Gopal Dass Estates' VP arrested over Ardee City ‘irregularities’
news.para: The builder had been booked in two separate cases related to irregularities in the development of the Sector 52 township.

news.title: ED attaches 29 land parcels valued Rs 30 crore of Unitech Group
news.para: The land parcels are situated in sectors 96-98 in Uttar Pradesh's Noida. These land parcels were illegally allotted to Carnoustie Management (India) Pvt Ltd (CMPL) by Chandras of Unitech Group, the ED said on Thursday.

news.title: Hong Kong developer to research how to tackle chronic housing shortage
news.para: "Solving Hong Kong's deep-rooted housing issue is fundamental to the city's future growth," Adrian Cheng, chief executive of New World and chairman of the initiative, New World Build for Good, said in a statement.
